⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 82/120 – Flatten JSON with Nested Arrays

🎤 Interview Question

Each employee contains an array of skills inside the JSON.

Write PySpark code to display one row per skill.


---

📊 Input Dataset

emp_id	employee

101	{"name":"John","skills":["Python","SQL"]}
102	{"name":"Alice","skills":["Java","AWS"]}



---

✅ Expected Output

emp_id	name	skill

101	John	Python
101	John	SQL
102	Alice	Java
102	Alice	AWS



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import explode

df.select(
    "emp_id",
    "employee.name",
    explode("employee.skills").alias("skill")
).show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Why is explode() used?

Answer

Because skills is an array, and each element needs to become its own row.


---

Q2. Can nested arrays be exploded directly?

Answer

Yes.

explode("employee.skills")


---

Q3. Real-world use cases?

Answer

Product tags

Customer interests

User roles

Event attributes



